{
  "texts": [
    "One patient was receiving valproic acid (VPA) for mood disorder and was started on IV meropenem for sepsis due to one of two blood cultures being positive extended spectrum beta-lactamase (ESBL) producing Escherichia coli bacteremia.",
    "GPT-4 advised on switching to piperacillin-tazobactam therapy to avoid the significant DDI between VPA and meropenem; however, this would be an inappropriate antibiotic option given the severity of illness and resistance mechanism of ESBL Escherichia coli.",
    "In a patient receiving phenobarbital and apixaban, GPT-4 recommended either monitoring the patient for signs of reduced anticoagulant effect or switching to rivaroxaban, a medication that is susceptible to reduced levels from phenobarbital induction.",
    "In both patient case scenarios, GPT4 accurately identified and explained the DDI, but failed to provide an appropriate clinical recommendation when applying the knowledge to a case.",
    "While GPT-4 demonstrated promise in its ability to identify clinically relevant DDIs, application to clinical cases remains an area of investigation."
  ]
}